posts.cooked:
Hi!
I was thinking it might be useful to create a central page to help out users in countries where Signal is censored.

How to help?

  1. Read the blog post
  2. Let other users know here that you are running a proxy and folks can get in touch with you (I’d advise against sharing the link directly) - just post a reply

Need help?

  1. Make sure you’re running Signal for Android version 5.3.12 or above.
  2. If you are able to run your own proxy or you know someone you trust that can do that for you, do this first.
  3. If you don’t have anyone that can help you with this, reach out to someone that is running in the replies to this post via a private message. If possible report back to let them know if the proxy works in your country or not. They should share with you a link that looks like this: https://signal.tube/#… which you can then open with Signal to join the proxy.

Note: the person running the server cannot read your messages but they can see your IP.
